**Solution:**
We want to find the smallest value of $n$ that satisfies the following three congruences:
\begin{align*}
&n\equiv 1\pmod{6}\\
&n\equiv 1\pmod{7}\\
&n\equiv 1\pmod{8}
\end{align*}
Using the Chinese Remainder Theorem, we have
\begin{align*}
n&\equiv168x+1\pmod{6\cdot7\cdot8}\\
&\equiv168x+1\pmod{336}
\end{align*}
The smallest positive integer $n$ satisfying this congruence is $n=169$.
**Final Answer: $\boxed{169}$. I hope it is correct.**

